headline: Singapore cenbank fines JPMorgan $1.8 million over misconduct by relationship managers
summary: Singapore's central bank on Monday said it fined U.S. lender JPMorgan Chase a civil penalty of S$2.4 million for failing to prevent and detect misconduct committed by its relationship managers. ...

headline: Trump’s Commerce Pick Hawked Buzzy Investments That Went Bust
summary: Cantor Fitzgerald CEO  Howard Lutnick  was pitching a startup that said it made a key component of self-driving cars, which would soon be valued at $2 billion.  “I’m brilliantly successful because I select brilliantly,” Lutnick said during a 2021 video call selling investors on  AEye  which had almost no revenue at the time.  Lutnick was behind a blank-check company, or SPAC, that planned to merge with AEye to take it public.

headline: 1 High-Yield Dividend ETF I Plan to Buy Hand Over Fist in December
summary: One of my many passive income strategies is investing in exchange-traded funds (ETFs) that offer high income yields, like the JPMorgan Equity Premium Income ETF (NYSEMKT: JEPI).  The JPMorgan Equity Premium Income ETF has a dual mandate.  On top of that, it aims to provide equity market exposure with less volatility.
